comments: Wiggins (OKC) extends his leg out and makes intentional foot to ball contact.

Replay review of the foul called on Ivey (DET) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Williams (OKC) beats Ivey (DET) to the spot and establishes a legal guarding position prior to Ivey (DET) delivering the contact during the driving shot attempt.
Wiggins (OKC) brings his hands toward Joseph (DET) and marginal contact occurs as Wiggins (OKC) releases away to roll.
Hampton (DET) does not establish himself in Williams' (OKC) path and delivers illegal contact during the screen.
Williams (OKC) moves alongside Wiseman's (DET) path and maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Hampton (DET) and Wiggins (OKC) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.

At the end of the drive, Bagley III (DET) cleanly dislodges the ball from Williams (OKC) and while the ball is loose, Williams goes through Omoruyi's (DET) space. A loose ball foul is correctly called on Williams.
Joseph (DET) and Williams (OKC) briefly get their arms tangled and marginal contact occurs as they disengage at the start of the drive.
Omoruyi (DET) makes clean contact with the ball on his dislodge attempt during Williams' (OKC) driving shot attempt.
Wiseman (DET) brings his arm down and makes contact with Williams' (OKC) head, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Omoruyi (DET) initiates contact with Giddey's (OKC) body by wrapping his arm around Giddey's back, which affects his driving shot attempt.
After the rebound, Dort (OKC) and Omoruyi (DET) make clean contact with the ball to tie it up and a jump ball is correctly called.
After the gather, Hampton (DET) makes clean contact with the ball on his dislodge attempt during Giddey's (OKC) shot attempt near the basket.
Wiseman (DET) legally contests Giddey's (OKC) shot attempt near the basket.
Livers (DET) and Dort (OKC) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Livers (DET) contests the putback shot attempt and avoids making contact with Williams' (OKC) arm.
